Currently, it will be great if wild card is supported in Artifact directory field. This will help user to gather artifact from different directory for example
{code}
/*-webapp/target
{code}
This will gather artifact from VPN-webapp and ssh-webapp directory.

Currently, user is unable to startup Bamboo server  with jetty.xml due to the default setting being ship with Bamboo installation:
{code}
<SystemProperty name="bamboo.webapp" default="./webapp"/>
{code} 

Where the above tag should be:
{code}
<SystemProperty name="bamboo.webapp" default="../webapp"/>
{code}

It will be great if we could change the above tag in the installation distribution before distribute to user.

Lastly, it would be great if the default jetty.xml comes with SSL configuration as mentioned in the following documentation:
* http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Running+Bamboo+over+HTTPS

h5. Use case
A task may define some *custom build variable* that would need to later be retrieved in subsequent tasks. 
The current mechanism to handle this is to share artifacts between the tasks - the problem with this approach is that the "native" bamboo tasks, such as the ant task could not access this "custom build variables"; we would need to write a wrapper script that parses the artifact then invoked the ant command.

h5. Tested case
I created custom build variables using the variableDefinitionManager
{code}
VariableDefinition vd = new VariableDefinitionImpl();
vd.setPlan(plan); 
vd.setVariableType(VariableType.PLAN);
vd.setKey(k);
vd.setValue(v);
variableDefinitions.add( vd );
 variableDefinitionManager.saveVariableDefinitions(variableDefinitions);
{code}

h5. what currently works:

*Pass variables between tasks
{noformat}
   Plan
      Stage 1
          Job1
              task 1A: set_plan_variable myVar
              task 1B : print_variable myVar
{noformat}

h5. What does not work:
* Pass variables between a jobs (expected not to work since jobs can be concurrent)

* Pass variables between a stages
{noformat}
   Plan
      Stage 1
          Job1
              task 1A: set_plan_variable myVar
      Stage 2:
          Job1
              task 2A : print_variable myVar
{noformat}
